comment: This lemma is used to prove that ` x ` built as in Lemma 2 of [BrosowskiDeutsh] p. 91, is such that x < ε on ` A ` . Here ` X ` is used to represent ` x ` in the paper, ` E ` is used to represent ε in the paper, and ` D ` is used to represent ` A ` in the paper (because ` A ` is always used to represent the subalgebra). (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 20-Apr-2017.)
